The program is supposed to print out all matched item ids from a list of it
items and also keep track of the most recent matching item. The issue here 
appears to be that it doesn't update lastMatch when encountering a new matc
match, which leads to printing "none" every time there are no matches in th
the current loop iteration. 

Here is the fixed version:
```tundra
val items = [
   { id: 4, matched: true },
   { id: 5, matched: false },
   { id: 7, matched: true }
];

var lastMatch = "none";
for(item in items) {
  if (item.matched) {
    print(item.id);
    lastMatch = item.id; // Update lastMatch when finding a match
  }
}

print(lastMatch);
```
This program will correctly identify the matched items and remember the mos
most recent one by assigning it to `lastMatch` variable after printing each
each matching id. It also includes print of final value of `lastMatch`, whi
which should be the latest item's id if any matches were found in the list.
list. If no matches were found, `lastMatch` will still contain "none".
